          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "This film is a recording of a live performance from 1983 at the Centro de Bellas Artes in San Juan, Puerto Rico. It explores Puerto Rico’s tri‑ethnic heritage and features multiple Indigenous musical genres, including bomba, plena, and danza. The performance includes renowned artists such as Don Rafael Cepeda and Petra Cepeda. It also addresses and portrays the history of slavery."
            }
          ]
        }
